The paper deals with stochastic optimal control, which is a topic that falls under the control systems (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of path integral methods for optimization is a common technique in machine learning and reinforcement learning, which are sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the interaction of multi-modal control with risk sensitivity, which is a topic that falls under robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE).
